Files

file  pcie.h
 This file contains the prototypes of the APIs present in the device abstraction layer file of PCIe. This also contains some related macros.

Macros

#define PCIECTRL_TI_CONF_IRQSTATUS_RAW_MAIN_ALL
 Macro containing mask of all the main interrupts. This macro can be passed to interrupt control API's to enable or disable all the main interrupts at a time.
 
#define PCIECTRL_TI_CONF_IRQSTATUS_RAW_MSI_ALL
 Macro containing mask of all the MSI interrupts. This macro can be passed to MSI interrupt control API's to enable or disable all the MSI interrupts at a time.

Detailed Description

Typedef Documentation

typedef struct pcieAtuRegionParams pcieAtuRegionParams_t

This Structure defines the ATU region parameters.

These parameters are used for configuring inbound or outbound ATU(Address translation unit) region

typedef struct pcieBarParams pcieBarParams_t

This structure defines BAR parameters.

These parameters are used for configuring BAR window

typedef struct pcieMsiCtrlParams pcieMsiCtrlParams_t

This structure defines MSI(Message signaled interrupt) Ctrl params.

These parameters are used to configure local or remote MSI capabilities.

typedef struct pcieMsiMailboxParams pcieMsiMailboxParams_t

This structure defines MSI(Message signaled interrupt) parameters.

These parameters are used to configure local RC's MSI mailbox or remote EP's MSI descriptor.

typedef struct pcieTrafficCtrlParams pcieTrafficCtrlParams_t

PCIe traffic control parameter structure.

These parameters are used to control PCIe Traffic. Pass 1 to enable and 0 to disable the control parameter.

Function Documentation

void PCIEAtuRegionConfig ( uint32_t  baseAddr,
const pcieLocationParams_t *  locationParams,
uint32_t  atuRegionIndex,
const pcieAtuRegionParams_t *  atuRegionParams 
)

Configures PCIe outbound or inbound region.

Parameters
baseAddrBase Address of the PCIeSS registers.
locationParamsRefer struct pcieLocationParams_t for details
atuRegionIndexregion to be configured
  • Possible values for inbound configuration 0 to 3
  • Possible values for outbound configuration 0 to 15
atuRegionParamsATU region parameters. Values given by struct pcieAtuRegionParams_t.
Returns
None
Note
This API will configure 32-bit aligned addresses.
void PCIEBarConfig ( uint32_t  baseAddr,
const pcieLocationParams_t *  locationParams,
uint32_t  barNumber,
const pcieBarParams_t *  barParams 
)

This function configures the BAR.

Parameters
baseAddrBase Address of the PCIeSS registers.
locationParamsstructure to select local or remote cfg space Refer struct pcieLocationParams_t for details.
barNumberBAR number to be configured Possible values for 32 bit BAR for RC are 0 and 1 Possible values for 32 bit BAR for EP are 0 to 5 Possible values for 64 bit BAR for RC is 0 Possible values for 64 bit BAR for EP are 0 to 2
barParamsBAR configuration parameters. Refer struct pcieBarParams_t for details
Returns
None
Note
This API should be called only after setting the PCIe device type.
